<h1>Adding Books</h1>
<p>
<strong>dslibris</strong> will find all XHTML files with extensions .xht or .xhtml that are in your media's book directory. These books will show up in the book browser.
</p>
<h1>Library Controls</h1>
<p><strong>DPAD-UP</strong> and <strong>DPAD-DOWN</strong> select books.</p>
<p><strong>A</strong>, <strong>DPAD-RIGHT</strong> or <strong>tap</strong> to open the selected book.</p>
<h1>Reading Controls</h1>
<p><strong>A</strong>,<strong>R</strong>,<strong>DPAD-RIGHT</strong> or tap on on the right half of the touchscreen to advance one page.</p>
<p><strong>B</strong>,<strong>L</strong>,<strong>DPAD-LEFT</strong> or tap on the left half of the touchscreen to retreat a page.</p>
<p><strong>X</strong> inverts the screen color.</p>
<p><strong>Y</strong> cycles through screen brightnesses on the DS Lite.</p>
<p><strong>SELECT</strong> returns to the library browser.</p>
<p><strong>START</strong> toggles a bookmark on the current page.</p>
<p><strong>DPAD-UP</strong> and <strong>DPAD_DOWN</strong> cycle through bookmarks.</p>
